<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Servile" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Servile,</orth> slavish: <bibl n="shak. luc 295" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 295</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.185" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 185</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 18</bibl> (Ff <emph>idle</emph>). <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 21</bibl>. With <emph>to,</emph> == meanly subject: <cit><quote>s. to my coy disdain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 112" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 112</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>subject and s. to all discontents,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 112" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 112</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>s. to all the skyey influences,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 9</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>